Specification for Event Planning App

Overview
This document outlines the specifications for the development of an event planning application. 

Features
User Registration: Users should be able to create an account and log in to the application.
Event Creation: Users should be able to create new events and set event details such as date, time, location, and type of event.
Guest Management: Users should be able to manage guests by adding, editing, or deleting guest details such as name, email, and phone number.
Budget Management: Users should be able to manage event budget by setting a budget and tracking expenses.
Vendor Management: Users should be able to manage vendors by adding, editing, or deleting vendor details such as name, contact information, and payment information.
Calendar View: Users should be able to view events on a calendar, including event details such as date, time, and location.

Technologies

Programming Language: React Native.
Database: Firebase.

Conclusion
This document outlines the specifications for the development of an event planning application. By incorporating these features and technologies, the application should be able to provide users with a comprehensive tool for planning and organizing events.
